0.title: Villians & Valors Rules
0.body:
Expansion Game Setup

With the added Event Cards you can now construction the Event Deck to do this you will do the following steps:

·        Randomly Select 9 Freedom Squadron (Blue) Events, 9 VENOM (Yellow Events), 9 All is Quiet (Grey) and a 10 VENOM Strikes (Red) based on player count and shuffle it up.  This will be your Even Deck.

·        In a game of 2-3 Players, utilize the full event deck.

·        In a game of 4-5 players, remove all 9 “All is Quiet” events from the Even Deck.

·        You can change the Difficulty of the game up or down by doing the following.

o   If you want an easier game remove 4 VENOM Strikes from the Deck.

o   If you want a more challenging game then remove up 4 VENOM Strikes and replace them with the Enhanced VENOM Strikes Cards.  Be aware these are more powerful and will greatly increase your chances of losing.

 

New Terms

Fail Combat: This ability only occurs when you choose to battle a VENOM Leader and fail to defeat/Capture them.

Fortify: Place the specified number of Fortify Tokens on the specified location on the board.  During the Tactual Phase you will now have a, 8th step, this is where you will have a chance to remove these tokens.  A single token can be removed by discarding 1 dice from your combat pool at this point.  During the Combat Phase – After you roll your dice you must apply any Success to any remaining Tokens this is done by placing the successful dice on a token.    Once all tokens have had a dice placed on them, any remaining successes are now applied to the Leaders Health Stat as normal.  

Redemption: When you defeat a VENOM Leader who has a Redemption Card you may on your Recruitment Phase pay their Combine Defense and Health Stats in Recruitment Points to redeem them. Their VENOM Leader card is returned to the box and their Freedom Squadron Card is placed into your Discard Pile.

Hibernate: Shuffle this card into the VENOM Leader Deck and replace it with a new one and put it Face Down.
